SIMULATION FRAMEWORK: MULTI-LAYERED OBJECT-ORIENTED ARCHITECTURE
================================================================================

This document details the modular, node-based architecture designed for discrete 
event supply chain and product flow simulations using SimPy and Python.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ARCHITECTURAL OVERVIEW
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The framework moves away from monolithic scripts and hardcoded functions by 
utilizing a "Directed Acyclic Graph / Network Flow" paradigm. Components are 
decoupled into independent object classes divided into a 6-layer hierarchy. 
Each layer has a single responsibility and builds upon the layers beneath it.

                          +-----------------------------------+
                          |  Layer 6: Configuration Context   |
                          +-----------------------------------+
                                            |
                          +-----------------------------------+
                          |    Layer 5: Telemetry Observer    |
                          +-----------------------------------+
